en_213681_0	The Gazette imposing a minimum penalty of 25 thousand rupees for 7 traffic offences was issued today Driving without a valid license, drunk driving, and negligence to enter a railway level crossing, driving without a valid insurance, high speed, employing persons without a license to drive vehicles and overtaking by the left are the offenses which are stipulated under this new penalty.
en_213681_1	The Transport Ministry further said that in addition, the traffic penalty on the offenses such as underage driving, dangerous driving and using a mobile phone while driving will be increased soon.
